subSubSection.paragraph:
DIAGNOSIS: This species is diagnosed by its relatively large size (TBL> 
2.5 mm
), long male mandibular horn (when present and fully developed) that extends from the medial surface of the mandible in a moderate, oblique curve up and to right over the clypeus (figs. 19, 20), and male with the median lobe of the aedeagus in lateral aspect stout, curved, and with the apex abruptly anvilshaped and truncate (fig. 36).

DESCRIPTION: Body moderate to large (TBL = 
2.59–3.32 mm
), elongate (PNW/ TBL = 0.46–0.49), moderately contractile.
